{{Infobox artist | name = Leon Keer | image = 3d-lego-terracotta-army-leonkeer.jpg | imagesize = 300px | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = | birth_place = | death_date = | medium = 3D Street Painting, [[Art]] | nationality = | active = | genre = | subject = | influences = | influenced = | spouse = }}
'''Leon Keer''' (born 1980, [[Utrecht]], [[Netherlands]]) is a Dutch pop-surrealist artist.<ref>[http://www.leonkeer.com/category/paintings/mixed-media/]. surreal art collective</ref> He has created work on canvas and (''3D'') artwork on the streets across the world. Leon Keer is a leading artist in anamorphic [[street art]]. His art has been showcased in Europe, the United States, Russia, Mexico, the United Arab Emirates, Australia, New Zealand, and several Asian countries. In addition to using optical illusion, he often presents his art by adding new technologies, such as augmented reality and video mapping. The art is temporary, but the images are shared all over the world via social media.{{citation needed|date=February 2017}}
Leon generally paints contemporary themes which involves environmental concerns and raises questions about the livability in this world.
== Career == Leon Keer designs and creates [[two-dimensional|2-D]], [[three-dimensional|3-D]] and [[four-dimensional|4-D]] street art in the Netherlands and abroad. The 3-D Lego terracotta army is one of those creations.<ref name="3D lego terracotta army">[http://www.nrc.nl/nieuws/2011/11/12/nederlanders-tekenen-3d-terracotta-lego-leger-op-straat/], nrc: nederlanders tekenen 3D terracotta Lego-leger op straat.</ref><ref name="3d lego streetpainting">[http://www.curatedmag.com/news/2011/11/10/leon-keer-–-3d-lego-street-painting/], curated (daily news).</ref> It was painted at the 2011 international [[Sarasota Chalk Festival]].
At 2010 festival in [[Sarasota]] he made a surreal [[street painting]] with [[Little red riding hood]] and [[Alice in Wonderland]] together, fighting against evil as main characters in the image.<ref name="chalkfestival">{{cite web |url=http://www.chalkfestival.com/?p=1456 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2011-12-06 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120426022359/http://www.chalkfestival.com/?p=1456 |archivedate=2012-04-26 |df= }} International [[Sarasota Chalk Festival]] in [[Sarasota, Florida|Florida]].</ref>
The anamorphic painting Piggy Bank was a Japanese debut for Leon Keer in 2013 and a 3d street art debut for [[Fukuoka]].<ref name="Piggy Bank Optical Illusion">[http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/04/09/3d-street-art-leon-keer-chalk-graffiti-piggy-bank-in-japan_n_3047494.html], huffingtonpost: Leon Keer, Chalk Artist, Creates 'Piggy Bank' Optical Illusion In Japan.</ref>
Experimenting with [[Augmented Reality]] combined with anamorphic art <ref name="4D Street Art">[http://www.lostateminor.com/2013/04/21/4d-street-art/], lost at e minor: 4D Street Art.</ref>
Malta Gummy bears - artist Leon Keer created 3D art for Malta street art festival <ref name="3D Street art Gummy bears painting">[http://www.widewalls.ch/malta-gummy-bears-leon-keer-street-art-festival/] Widewalls: 3D Street art Gummy bears painting</ref>
Keer is often confused with [[Ego Leonard]],<ref name="lego-man-artist-revealed">[http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/nationnow/2011/11/lego-man-artist-revealed.html Lego Man artist revealed]</ref> the anonymous guerilla artist.<ref>[http://www.egoleonard.com Ego Leonard]</ref>
