This is a list of notable cases of '''[[Law enforcement in Pakistan|law enforcement]] brutality''' ({{lang-ur|'''قانون نافذ کرنے والے مظالم'''}}), including [[police brutality]] in Pakistan.
{{expand list|date=August 2012}} * 1960: Communist leader [[Hassan Nasir]] was killed during interrogation in [[Lahore Fort]].<ref name=Zia-and-after/> * 1980: Communist leader [[Nazeer Abbasi]] was one of many who died under interrogation during the martial law of [[Muhammad Zia-ul-Haq]].<ref name=Zia-and-after>{{cite book |last1=Hyman |first1=Anthony |last2=Ghayur |first2=Muhammed |last3=Kaushik |first3=Naresh |date=1989 |title=Pakistan, Zia and After-- |url={{Google books|plainurl=y|id=cjPgESaC-7sC|page=44|text=died during police and army interrogation.}} |location=New Delhi |publisher=Abhinav Publications |page=44 |isbn=81-7017-253-5}}</ref> * 2011: in the [[Kharotabad Incident]], five Russian and Tajik citizens were shot dead by [[Frontier Corps]] and police after falsely being reported as suicide bombers when approaching a border checkpoint. Dr. Baqir Shah, a police surgeon who testified against the official story, was attacked at a restaurant in Quetta,<ref>{{cite news |title=Kharotabad killings: Surgeon attacked 'over testimony'’ |url=http://tribune.com.pk/story/188619/kharotabad-shooting-incident-police-surgeon-tortured/ |newspaper=The Express Tribune |date=2011-06-14 |accessdate=2012-08-03}}</ref> and later shot dead by unknown gunmen.<ref>{{cite news |title=Kharotabad killings: Police surgeon shot dead in Quetta |url=http://www.dawn.com/2011/12/29/kharotabad-killings-police-surgeon-shot-dead-in-quetta.html |newspaper=Dawn |date=2011-12-29 |accessdate=2012-08-03}}</ref> * 2015: Two young brothers, Zeshan and Shakeel, were killed in police firing near Holy Family Hospital in Rawalpindi. Sources said Zeshan and Shakeel were returning home from work when police signaled them to stop at a checkpoint. Upon refusal, they were shot several times. One of them died instantly while other brother succumbed to injuries upon reaching the hospital. Both victims were unarmed.<ref>{{cite news |title=Police shoot dead two brothers for allegedly failing to stop for security checks in Pindi |url=http://tribune.com.pk/story/899262/police-shoot-dead-two-brothers-for-allegedly-failing-to-stop-for-security-checks/ |newspaper=The Express Tribune |date=2015-06-07}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Rawalpindi: two young brothers killed in police firing |url=http://www.geo.tv/article-187222-Rawalpindi-two-young-brothers-killed-in-police-firing- |work=Geo News |agency=Agence France-Presse |date=2015-06-07}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Two police officers held for shooting two brothers in Rawalpindi |url=http://dunyanews.tv/index.php/en/Pakistan/283202-Two-police-officers-held-for-shooting-two-brothers |work=Dunya News}}</ref> * [[Human rights violations in Balochistan]] which involves killings, false arrests and torture by law enforcement including the military and [[Paramilitary forces of Pakistan|paramilitary forces]]. * [[Human rights violations in Sindh]] which involves similar activities of the law enforcement agencies involved. The military and paramilitary have also been reportedly been in many of these instances. ==References== {{Reflist}}
