'''West Mallee''' is a [[statistical subdivision]] defined under the [[Australian Standard Geographical Classification]], and therefore used by the [[Australian Bureau of Statistics]]. It is one of three subdivisions of the [[Mallee (statistical division)|Mallee]] [[statistical division]] of the [[states and territories of Australia|Australian state]] of [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]]. It consists of three [[statistical local area]]s: [[Buloke (S) - North]], [[Buloke (S) - South]] and [[Mildura (RC) - Pt B]].<ref name="ASGC 2006">{{cite web | title = 1216.0 - Statistical Geography Volume 1 - Australian Standard Geographical Classification (ASGC), Jul 2006 | year = 2006 | publisher = [[Australian Bureau of Statistics]] | url = http://www.abs.gov.au/AUSSTATS/abs@.nsf/Latestproducts/1216.0Main%20Features1Jul%202006?opendocument | accessdate = 2007-04-26}}</ref>

